ARCHITECTURE.md
     1‚Üí# `sqlite-vec` Architecture
     3‚ÜíInternal documentation for how `sqlite-vec` works under-the-hood. Not meant for
     4‚Üíusers of the `sqlite-vec` project, consult
     5‚Üí[the official `sqlite-vec` documentation](https://alexgarcia.xyz/sqlite-vec) for
     6‚Üíhow-to-guides. Rather, this is for people interested in how `sqlite-vec` works
     7‚Üíand some guidelines to any future contributors.
     8‚Üí
     9‚ÜíVery much a WIP.
    10‚Üí
    11‚Üí## `vec0`
    13‚Üí### Shadow Tables
    49‚Üí### idxStr
    51‚ÜíThe `vec0` idxStr is a string composed of single "header" character and 0 or
    52‚Üímore "blocks" of 4 characters each.
    53‚Üí
    54‚ÜíThe "header" charcter denotes the type of query plan, as determined by the
    55‚Üí`enum vec0_query_plan` values. The current possible values are:
    56‚Üí
    57‚Üí| Name                       | Value | Description                                                            |
    58‚Üí| -------------------------- | ----- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶

README.md
     1‚Üí# `sqlite-vec`
     5‚ÜíAn extremely small, "fast enough" vector search SQLite extension that runs
     6‚Üíanywhere! A successor to [`sqlite-vss`](https://github.com/asg017/sqlite-vss)
     7‚Üí
     8‚Üí<!-- deno-fmt-ignore-start -->
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí> [!IMPORTANT]
    11‚Üí> _`sqlite-vec` is a pre-v1, so expect breaking changes!_
    12‚Üí
    13‚Üí<!-- deno-fmt-ignore-end -->
    14‚Üí
    15‚Üí- Store and query float, int8, and binary vectors in `vec0` virtual tables
    16‚Üí- Written in pure C, no dependencies, runs anywhere SQLite runs
    17‚Üí  (Linux/MacOS/Windows, in the browser with WASM, Raspberry Pis, etc.)
    18‚Üí- Store non-vector data in metadata, auxiliary, or partition key columns
    19‚Üí
    20‚Üí<p align="center">
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
